www.addic7ed.com

00:04.553 --> 00:05.462
Get up!

00:05.889 --> 00:06.769
Get up!

00:07.091 --> 00:08.730
First day of school!
I mean it, people!

00:08.851 --> 00:10.729
We are not gonna be
the la-- Oh.

00:11.153 --> 00:13.123
- You're up already.
- Yep.

00:13.238 --> 00:14.626
Turns out with no Axl

00:14.736 --> 00:16.447
pulling his dirty underwear
over my head

00:16.545 --> 00:19.731
yelling, "Time's up!" and
dragging me out of the bathroom,

00:19.835 --> 00:21.229
I had time to shower
this morning.

00:21.355 --> 00:23.949
I was even able to
rinse and repeat.

00:24.207 --> 00:25.357
Get up!

00:25.439 --> 00:27.064
First day of school!
Get up!

00:27.157 --> 00:29.070
I'm sick of-- Oh.

00:29.171 --> 00:30.194
They're up already.

00:30.289 --> 00:31.840
I couldn't sleep anyway,
it was so hot.

00:31.951 --> 00:33.572
When are we getting
the air conditioner fixed?

00:33.755 --> 00:35.180
I tried
packing myself in popsicles,

00:35.275 --> 00:36.819
but I woke up covered in ants.

00:36.926 --> 00:39.392
I told you, you don't fix the
air conditioner when it's hot.

00:39.483 --> 00:41.973
You wait till winter when
the AC guys are desperate,

00:42.077 --> 00:43.361
and then you get a discount.

00:43.570 --> 00:46.524
That's why I'm going tomorrow
to look at snowblowers.

00:46.794 --> 00:49.289
Is that why you guys didn't
buy us any school supplies?

00:49.379 --> 00:50.381
No.
That we just forgot.

00:50.618 --> 00:52.599
Look, you can get them in a
couple weeks when they're cheap.

00:52.868 --> 00:54.466
Meantime, you can just
borrow from friends.

00:54.641 --> 00:57.678
Um, that'll be probably be
more of a two-step process.

00:58.877 --> 00:59.994
What are you doing?

01:00.082 --> 01:02.661
Texting Axl to remind him
he has Philosophy at 9:00.

01:02.749 --> 01:04.226
You know,
he's not a morning person.

01:04.328 --> 01:05.804
Come on.
He's a big boy, Frankie.

01:05.959 --> 01:07.443
He doesn't need mommy
waking him up.

01:10.935 --> 01:13.298
I've been thinking, why do I need
to go to middle school, anyway?

01:13.491 --> 01:14.678
You know,
I've done some research,

01:14.765 --> 01:16.580
and homeschooling
is not out of the question.

01:16.678 --> 01:17.582
It is at this home.

01:17.680 --> 01:19.142
What now, Brick?

01:19.295 --> 01:20.627
Is this about the asbestos
again?

01:20.702 --> 01:23.089
'Cause I told you, they got that
down to acceptable levels.

01:23.266 --> 01:24.744
Okay, I'd be lying if I said

01:24.845 --> 01:26.273
I didn't have some concerns,

01:26.456 --> 01:28.913
not the least of which is
I can't go to the bathroom.

01:29.013 --> 01:30.900
Unh-unh.
No more quirks. You're done.

01:31.032 --> 01:31.932
It's not that.

01:32.082 --> 01:34.242
Everyone knows if a sixth grader
goes to the bathroom,

01:34.380 --> 01:36.595
eighth graders wait in there
to give him a swirlie.

01:36.702 --> 01:38.940
Brick, that's just a
stupid legend that goes around.

01:39.039 --> 01:40.935
That stuff doesn't really
happen. Mike, tell him.

01:41.020 --> 01:42.987
Did you ever in your whole life
get a swirlie?

01:43.161 --> 01:44.462
I didn't <i>get</i> them.

01:44.769 --> 01:45.745
You'll be fine.

01:46.286 --> 01:47.916
<i>While Brick was worried</i>
<i>about getting swirlied,</i>

01:48.049 --> 01:49.832
<i>Sue wasn't worried</i>
<i>about a thing.</i>

01:49.940 --> 01:50.968
Oh, my God.

01:51.066 --> 01:52.439
This feels amazing!

01:52.625 --> 01:55.711
I can't believe I'm actually
getting to walk down this hall.

01:55.808 --> 01:57.040
I know. Me too.

01:57.273 --> 01:58.504
Wait. Why?

01:58.752 --> 02:00.562
Axl's locker was on this hall,

02:00.657 --> 02:02.414
and he would never
let me walk down it,

02:02.548 --> 02:04.589
even though I had a class here.

02:04.751 --> 02:06.777
I would have to go outside,
and the old crossing guard

02:06.878 --> 02:09.424
would lift me up so I could
crawl through the window.

02:09.652 --> 02:12.085
Sue, we don't have
a crossing guard.

02:12.403 --> 02:14.367
Huh.
Then who was that?

02:14.459 --> 02:16.477
Anyway, I am free now.

02:16.620 --> 02:18.288
I can go wherever I want.

02:18.407 --> 02:19.969
I can do whatever I want.

02:20.133 --> 02:22.360
I can even
dance down this hallway,

02:22.458 --> 02:24.643
and there's no one here
to call me a dork.

02:24.737 --> 02:26.896
- You don't have to ask me twice!
- Whoo!

02:29.261 --> 02:30.777
Hey.

02:30.878 --> 02:31.914
Just getting home from work?

02:32.244 --> 02:34.432
Yep. Had to
catch up on some things.

02:34.539 --> 02:35.501
Uh-huh.

02:35.620 --> 02:37.776
You were sitting in the car with the
air-conditioning on, weren't you?

02:37.890 --> 02:40.556
Hey, you're always saying
you want some alone time,

02:40.690 --> 02:43.258
and I didn't know we were putting
frozen chicken down our shirts.

02:43.365 --> 02:44.895
Not when it's 100 degrees.

02:45.004 --> 02:47.862
When it's hot, I want
people around to complain to.

02:47.997 --> 02:49.060
Ugh.

02:49.152 --> 02:50.603
I can never get ahold of Axl.

02:50.688 --> 02:52.766
I swear,
this kid never texts me back.

02:52.869 --> 02:54.243
I don't hear from him anymore.

02:54.480 --> 02:56.085
What do you need to get in touch
with him for, anyway?

02:56.192 --> 02:57.763
Well, for one, he's my son,

02:57.865 --> 02:59.374
and I'd like to know
he's been eating.

02:59.555 --> 03:01.398
He's fine, Frankie.
He's an athlete.

03:01.502 --> 03:03.067
The coaches make sure
they eat right.

03:07.400 --> 03:08.999
Well, it's not just that.

03:09.112 --> 03:11.151
There's been some mix-up in his
schedule, and I need to make sure

03:11.253 --> 03:13.067
that he transferred out of
Intro to Sosh.

03:13.168 --> 03:14.717
You know what?
I'm just gonna call him.

03:15.069 --> 03:16.577
Hey, buddy.
How was--

03:16.669 --> 03:17.737
Bathroom.
Bathroom.

03:17.833 --> 03:19.546
Bathroom.
Bathroom.

03:21.878 --> 03:23.448
- He's not picking up.
- Hey, pal.

03:23.591 --> 03:26.499
Did you ever transfer
out of Intro to Sosh?

03:26.598 --> 03:29.230
Done. You know a cool thing
about being a football player?

03:29.324 --> 03:32.151
They sent some kid over to do it
for me 'cause I'm, like, way busy.

03:32.288 --> 03:34.058
- Sweet!
- All right, then.

03:34.157 --> 03:35.376
I'm gonna let you go.

03:36.462 --> 03:38.344
What was that?
He answered?

03:38.452 --> 03:40.393
- Yeah.
- What do you mean, "Yeah"?

03:40.581 --> 03:42.674
- Does he usually answer?
- Yeah.

03:42.853 --> 03:43.872
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

03:44.033 --> 03:46.505
Okay, so, you're saying
when you text him,

03:46.679 --> 03:49.030
- he texts you back?
- Yeah.

03:49.220 --> 03:50.742
Oh, my God.

03:50.868 --> 03:51.918
We have any dip?

03:52.064 --> 03:53.663
No, we don't
have any dip, Mike.

03:53.824 --> 03:55.699
I can't believe
Axl has been texting you

03:55.793 --> 03:58.260
this whole time
and he won't text me!

03:58.385 --> 03:59.939
Oh, come on.
He's texted you.

04:00.039 --> 04:01.927
Oh, I'm sorry.
I was wrong.

04:02.026 --> 04:03.368
I did get one text.

04:03.460 --> 04:05.728
It said, "K-D-J-J-J."

04:05.842 --> 04:06.930
Pretty sure it was a butt text.

04:07.033 --> 04:09.346
So, yes,
I have heard from Axl's butt.

04:09.495 --> 04:10.667
Well, that's something.

04:11.814 --> 04:14.421
I just don't get it, Mike!

04:14.667 --> 04:16.742
Why won't he text me back?!

04:16.869 --> 04:18.307
Why is he doing this to me?!

04:18.440 --> 04:20.594
Why won't he answer my calls?!

04:20.711 --> 04:22.583
Maybe 'cause of
that voice right there?

04:22.745 --> 04:24.967
I'm just saying,
moms can be kind of clingy.

04:25.097 --> 04:26.439
You got to be
cooler about this.

04:26.768 --> 04:28.635
I'm... cool.

04:28.768 --> 04:30.415
Look, you can't
text him all the time.

04:30.510 --> 04:31.838
You got to space them out.

04:31.929 --> 04:32.806
And if you just called him,

04:32.928 --> 04:34.677
maybe wait a couple days before
you call him again.

04:34.870 --> 04:36.314
Oh, and be sure to
hang up first.

04:36.406 --> 04:37.682
You don't want to be
the rambly one.

04:37.867 --> 04:39.451
You want to
make him come to you.

04:39.742 --> 04:41.621
I'm not trying to date my son.

04:41.796 --> 04:44.546
Trust me, Frankie, you just got
to give him time to miss you.

04:46.802 --> 04:48.866
But that could take years!

04:53.352 --> 04:55.483
Why is this thing
even on, Mike?

04:55.591 --> 04:58.173
That vent's just blowing
air from the outside.

04:58.289 --> 05:00.775
Look, you need the airflow
to cool you off when you sweat.

05:00.874 --> 05:02.301
It's nature's
air-conditioning.

05:02.396 --> 05:03.607
I don't want
nature's air-conditioning.

05:03.695 --> 05:05.502
I want
people's air-conditioning.

05:06.067 --> 05:08.286
Thanks, but I'm off liquids
until June.

05:08.466 --> 05:10.922
I'm training myself
not to go to the bathroom.

05:11.028 --> 05:12.673
Brick, you need to
drink something.

05:12.769 --> 05:14.067
Your kidneys
are gonna shut down,

05:14.156 --> 05:15.547
and we can't afford that.

05:15.644 --> 05:17.529
Why are you still sitting
in a lawn chair, Brick?

05:17.670 --> 05:19.803
You know, you don't have to be
in a lawn chair

05:19.889 --> 05:21.756
when there's a perfectly good
chair right there.

05:22.025 --> 05:24.437
Unh-unh. That's Axl's.
No way.

05:24.625 --> 05:26.063
Well, he's gone now.

05:26.267 --> 05:30.791
Finally, we are the size family
we were always meant to be.

05:33.405 --> 05:34.747
What?

05:34.882 --> 05:36.493
I thought
I heard my phone buzz.

05:37.810 --> 05:39.220
Look, it's been radio silence,

05:39.314 --> 05:40.587
and I've done
everything you said.

05:40.693 --> 05:42.211
I have been so good.

05:42.332 --> 05:44.345
I went for two days
without calling him.

05:44.492 --> 05:46.571
I waited 36 hours between texts

05:46.713 --> 05:49.336
and not one word back--
nothing.

05:49.489 --> 05:51.469
I said, "How'z it hanging?"
With a "Z."

05:51.579 --> 05:53.069
It doesn't get
more casual than that.

05:53.190 --> 05:55.724
I followed your stupid rules
and nothing--

05:55.824 --> 05:57.313
I still get nothing.

05:57.621 --> 05:59.274
Look, it's like I said before,
Frankie.

05:59.362 --> 06:00.538
You're too needy.

06:00.677 --> 06:02.267
Guys can smell that,
and they run.

06:02.361 --> 06:04.000
I can't help it.
I miss my son.

06:04.082 --> 06:05.202
It's normal to miss your son.

06:05.303 --> 06:06.413
It's normal for him to be gone.

06:06.580 --> 06:07.911
So you're saying
you don't miss him at all?

06:08.079 --> 06:10.755
I'm saying
it's how it's supposed to be.

06:11.441 --> 06:13.856
I mean, I-I'm perfectly fine
with him being gone.

06:14.039 --> 06:15.456
I'd be fine
if these two were gone.

06:15.724 --> 06:16.878
Right here, dad.

06:17.004 --> 06:18.416
- You know what I mean.
- Mm.

06:18.583 --> 06:20.124
Dad's right.
I'm just gonna say it.

06:20.296 --> 06:22.158
I am glad that Axl's gone.

06:22.268 --> 06:24.111
And I'm not sorry
for saying it, either.

06:24.229 --> 06:27.151
He insulted me
roughly 56 times a day,

06:27.266 --> 06:28.446
and that's being conservative.

06:28.579 --> 06:31.413
I mean, you guys have no idea
how many times it happened.

06:31.662 --> 06:34.039
- Dork says, "Hey."
- Hey!

06:34.209 --> 06:36.241
I'm sorry, but I'm a huge
supporter of animal rights,

06:36.345 --> 06:39.050
and I just think it's wrong
to put a monkey in clothes.

06:39.315 --> 06:41.041
Which finger smells like butt?

06:41.135 --> 06:42.510
Which finger
smells like butt, huh?

06:42.610 --> 06:44.275
Trick question.
They all do.

06:44.369 --> 06:46.205
- Aah!
- Aggh!

06:46.712 --> 06:48.185
But that's all in the past now.

06:48.340 --> 06:50.517
Axl's reign of terror is over.

06:50.907 --> 06:52.848
We're done
being called Pew and Ick.

06:52.995 --> 06:54.586
We are done cleaning his room

06:54.689 --> 06:57.096
only to find out
there was no 10 bucks!

06:57.250 --> 06:59.960
Our time has come, Brick. If you
won't sit in his chair, I will!

07:06.121 --> 07:07.371
We're free now.

07:07.738 --> 07:09.757
Our brother
can't hurt us anymore.

07:12.432 --> 07:14.482
Still better than
having him here.

