just do what you can, Darrin.

07:46.757 --> 07:48.254
Limp it along till December.

07:48.420 --> 07:49.855
Okay, but just so you know,

07:50.022 --> 07:51.832
I wouldn't feel right
about taking your money.

07:52.144 --> 07:53.748
Good, 'cause
I can't give you any.

07:59.136 --> 08:01.067
I can't take it!
I got to go!

08:01.166 --> 08:02.882
Are you crazy?
You can't go to the bathroom.

08:03.019 --> 08:04.936
Don't you know what happens
to kids who go in there?

08:05.075 --> 08:06.667
I heard there's
an old eighth grader in there

08:06.808 --> 08:08.948
who never graduated,
and if you try to run from him,

08:09.097 --> 08:11.296
your feet get stuck to the floor
because of all the pee.

08:11.458 --> 08:13.955
Well, I heard about someone
getting a royal flush.

08:14.134 --> 08:15.611
That's a double swirlie!

08:15.773 --> 08:17.300
He drank so much toilet water

08:17.445 --> 08:18.891
that eggs grew in his stomach.

08:19.046 --> 08:20.332
And when he
went to the hospital

08:20.440 --> 08:21.734
to get them
removed from his stomach,

08:21.898 --> 08:23.970
spiders crawled out.

08:28.329 --> 08:29.435
Oh.

08:30.032 --> 08:30.973
Hi.

08:31.078 --> 08:31.974
Hi!

08:37.866 --> 08:39.952
What's with us and trash, huh?

08:40.051 --> 08:41.750
Yeah.
It's like we're flies.

08:41.895 --> 08:43.003
Yeah.

08:43.342 --> 08:44.871
So, wow.

08:45.008 --> 08:46.473
I didn't even
realize you were here.

08:46.729 --> 08:48.515
The first rule of
being a good service technician

08:48.726 --> 08:51.585
is not disturbing
the occupants of the dwelling.

08:53.735 --> 08:55.834
Anyway, so, how's school going?

08:56.052 --> 08:57.135
Oh, it's great.

08:57.266 --> 08:59.330
Uh, I have a ton of
responsibilities this year.

08:59.534 --> 09:02.780
You may have heard--
I am a Junior Peer Leadership Adviser.

09:02.886 --> 09:04.653
You know, a JP-la.

09:04.757 --> 09:07.028
Yeah. I don't think
I knew they had those.

09:07.885 --> 09:09.086
Anyway,

09:09.197 --> 09:13.294
look at you,
Mr. Repairman... man.

09:13.392 --> 09:14.750
Yeah. And look at you.

09:15.041 --> 09:16.436
You do something different
with your hair?

09:16.552 --> 09:18.303
Oh, I'm rinsing
and repeating now.

09:18.487 --> 09:19.485
Me too.

09:19.614 --> 09:20.792
A lot of work goes into this.

09:26.392 --> 09:29.345
Well, I should probably
get going.

09:29.437 --> 09:32.175
You know, all the
JP-la responsibilities.

09:32.330 --> 09:34.572
And I should probably get back
to not being able to fix this.

09:36.931 --> 09:39.950
Okay. Well, bye.

09:40.118 --> 09:41.450
Bye.

09:41.742 --> 09:42.728
Uh, Sue?

09:42.831 --> 09:44.074
Mm-hmm?

09:46.166 --> 09:48.222
Oh.

09:52.914 --> 09:55.818
Oh, hey. Want to hear
an interesting conversation?

09:55.977 --> 09:56.908
Not especially.

09:57.023 --> 09:58.445
Mike-- "Call your mom."

09:58.568 --> 10:00.570
Axl-- "Ugh. Why?"

10:00.688 --> 10:02.118
What are you doing?
Is that my phone?

10:02.256 --> 10:05.452
Mike-- "'Cause she's your mom,
and she wants to hear from you."

10:05.582 --> 10:08.273
Axl-- "Why, does she have
extra nag minutes?"

10:08.392 --> 10:10.184
Mike-- "LOL".

10:10.340 --> 10:12.489
LOL?
You LOL'd that?

10:12.626 --> 10:14.192
You thought that was
laugh out loud?

10:14.299 --> 10:16.736
When have you ever
laughed out loud at anything?

10:16.900 --> 10:18.575
Look, I was just
trying to help you out.

10:18.696 --> 10:20.888
Oh, sure,
'cause your little marionette

10:20.983 --> 10:24.011
will only call his mom if the
puppet master pulls the strings?

10:24.188 --> 10:25.593
You know, this is why--

10:26.436 --> 10:27.771
Forget it.

10:27.918 --> 10:29.412
What? Say it.

10:29.549 --> 10:30.507
Nope. Don't want to.

10:30.591 --> 10:32.792
No, this is why what?

10:33.189 --> 10:34.626
Nobody wants to talk to me?

10:34.761 --> 10:37.228
You know what, Frankie?
This is dangerous territory.

10:37.329 --> 10:39.437
So, let's just forget it.
Now, give me my phone back.

10:39.539 --> 10:42.127
Yeah. Okay, okay, but just
h-h-h-hold on a second.

10:42.233 --> 10:43.554
Why? What are you doing?

10:43.668 --> 10:46.212
Hey, give-- give-- give me
the phone. Give it back!

10:46.327 --> 10:47.949
I want to see what you're doing.

10:48.045 --> 10:49.962
I-I am not kidding you.
You give me the stupid phone.

10:50.051 --> 10:51.351
- Hey! What are you, nuts?
- Give-- give--

10:51.453 --> 10:54.008
- What is this? - I don't know. How would
I know when it's not my phone?

10:54.109 --> 10:55.629
Oh, my God!

10:57.511 --> 10:59.706
Are you texting Axl as me?

10:59.831 --> 11:01.342
What?! No!

11:02.225 --> 11:03.741
"Hey, hotshot.

11:03.838 --> 11:05.358
How about that sports team?

11:05.516 --> 11:06.993
And are you
getting enough sleep?"

11:07.098 --> 11:09.214
- Frankie, really?
- Well, I'm sorry.

11:09.319 --> 11:10.454
I want to hear from my son,

11:10.560 --> 11:12.380
and I am not too proud
to pretend to be you to do it.

11:12.542 --> 11:13.927
I'm all left out in the cold

11:14.034 --> 11:15.998
while you two
are little texting buddies.

11:16.111 --> 11:18.088
Text, text, text.
"OMG".

11:18.194 --> 11:20.238
"LMAO".
"Dad's so awesome."

11:20.348 --> 11:22.110
"Smiley face.
Ha, ha, ha, ha, ha."

11:23.315 --> 11:25.855
Fine. Just forget it.
You can have each other.

11:25.977 --> 11:27.846
You just get off on your
little bicycle built for two

11:27.947 --> 11:29.486
and ride off into the sunset.

11:29.601 --> 11:31.739
Just remember this--
Sue likes me better,

11:31.878 --> 11:32.942
and when she
goes off to college,

11:33.052 --> 11:34.408
I'm gonna tell her
not to call you.

11:34.905 --> 11:36.680
What?!
But I love dad.

11:36.769 --> 11:38.048
I would never do that!

11:38.284 --> 11:40.178
Go to bed, Sue.

11:48.707 --> 11:51.235
<i>As more tall tales of the</i>
<i>bathroom swept through school,</i>

11:51.358 --> 11:53.667
<i>Brick's quest</i>
<i>to give up liquids continued.</i>

11:53.798 --> 11:56.011
<i>He survived the track unit</i>
<i>in gym class.</i>

11:56.120 --> 11:57.326
Ten more laps!

11:57.433 --> 11:59.265
And don't forget
to drink lots of water!

11:59.358 --> 12:00.477
It's hot!

12:02.942 --> 12:04.076
<i>He survived science class,</i>

12:04.214 --> 12:05.958
<i>where they were</i>
<i>studying the Sun.</i>

12:11.067 --> 12:14.350
<i>But what he hadn't counted on</i>
<i>was Ms. Harvey's fifth period.</i>

12:14.459 --> 12:16.157
Today, we are sampling foods

12:16.252 --> 12:18.169
from our neighbor
to the south--

