12:42.129 --> 12:43.145
Hey, Brad.

12:43.345 --> 12:44.717
I need to talk to you
about something.

12:44.897 --> 12:46.462
It's about Darrin.

12:46.564 --> 12:47.702
Ooh.

12:47.822 --> 12:49.454
I'll set the table.
You bring the dish.

12:49.561 --> 12:52.259
Okay, well, he came over
to our house yesterday.

12:52.382 --> 12:54.660
- What? Awkward.
- Yeah.

12:54.798 --> 12:55.932
At first.

12:56.052 --> 12:57.435
But then it was kind of nice.

12:57.580 --> 12:59.525
Kind of like
we'd never even broken up.

12:59.695 --> 13:02.785
It was like there was
this spark or something.

13:02.896 --> 13:04.377
And maybe this spark
is creating

13:04.490 --> 13:06.861
a blazing inferno
inside your heart?

13:07.035 --> 13:08.189
Maybe.

13:08.436 --> 13:10.117
It's just, I got to thinking.

13:10.288 --> 13:12.896
Darrin and I always
had a lot of fun together.

13:13.015 --> 13:16.832
We would play mini golf,
have crazy dance competitions,

13:16.963 --> 13:20.196
go through a drive-through
and order with British accents.

13:20.381 --> 13:22.699
The only reason
I really broke up with him

13:22.834 --> 13:25.341
was 'cause Axl
was being so weird about it.

13:25.468 --> 13:27.748
But I'm not living my life
for Axl anymore.

13:27.841 --> 13:29.113
Sue, when you
broke up with Darrin,

13:29.211 --> 13:31.879
I was all supportive, and I
said, "Uh-huh, uh-huh, uh-huh."

13:31.987 --> 13:33.741
But inside,
I was like, "No, no, no!"

13:33.872 --> 13:35.581
- So you think I should go for it?
- Uh-huh.

13:35.704 --> 13:38.649
And the real "Uh-huh."
Not the one with the screaming "No" inside.

13:42.781 --> 13:44.083
I can't hold it anymore.

13:44.196 --> 13:45.451
I'm going to the bathroom.

13:45.711 --> 13:47.175
No, you won't survive!

13:47.355 --> 13:48.651
Want to punch me in the eye?

13:48.767 --> 13:51.264
Then you can go to the vice principal's
office and use his bathroom.

13:51.411 --> 13:54.060
That's all the way to Building "A."
I'll never make it.

13:54.196 --> 13:56.137
Building "A."
Whoop!

13:56.282 --> 13:57.352
Try sneaking in.

13:57.468 --> 13:59.851
Maybe that way, you won't
draw attention to yourself.

14:01.339 --> 14:02.525
No.

14:03.232 --> 14:04.452
No sneaking.

14:04.589 --> 14:06.282
We're sixth graders.

14:06.484 --> 14:08.561
Yeah, we may not
have hair on our arms

14:08.663 --> 14:10.631
or the courage
to look a girl in the eye,

14:10.755 --> 14:13.791
and we sometimes yearn for
the days of scheduled nap time,

14:13.995 --> 14:15.747
but we're still men--

14:15.878 --> 14:18.947
small men,
but men nonetheless--

14:19.197 --> 14:21.892
and it's time to
start acting like it.

14:23.042 --> 14:24.596
<i>So Brick set out to go</i>

14:24.689 --> 14:27.088
<i>where no sixth grader</i>
<i>had ever gone before--</i>

14:27.689 --> 14:28.940
<i>the bathroom.</i>

14:53.745 --> 14:55.082
Hey, how's it going?

14:55.482 --> 14:56.756
Hey.

15:01.795 --> 15:03.411
