has happened.

15:05.140 --> 15:06.664
Maybe we should
go in and help him.

15:06.769 --> 15:08.604
You go.
Brick and I aren't that close.

15:16.386 --> 15:18.124
- Yes!
- All right!

15:18.229 --> 15:19.363
<i>So Brick was a hero,</i>

15:19.472 --> 15:22.433
<i>admired and respected</i>
<i>by his fellow classmates--</i>

15:22.551 --> 15:24.416
<i>for about 10 seconds until...</i>

15:35.698 --> 15:36.776
Hey, Mr. Heck.

15:36.890 --> 15:38.184
I've completed
a thorough diagnostic,

15:38.297 --> 15:41.220
and I've determined I have no
idea what's wrong with the unit.

15:41.371 --> 15:44.205
But on the plus side, we have a
class on condensers Tuesday,

15:44.335 --> 15:47.052
so here's hoping
it's the condenser, huh?

15:47.152 --> 15:49.026
Yeah, well, don't count on it.

15:49.239 --> 15:50.414
It's our house.

15:50.656 --> 15:52.405
So, hey,
the Colts game's about to start.

15:52.535 --> 15:53.633
Why don't you
stick around and watch?

15:53.723 --> 15:55.834
- Oh, that sounds great.
- All right!

15:56.713 --> 15:57.952
But I can't.

15:58.198 --> 15:59.640
Aw, come on.
I owe you.

15:59.763 --> 16:01.946
The Pacers are in preseason,
the Colts are in San Francisco,

16:02.075 --> 16:03.406
Brick just read our TV manual,

16:03.512 --> 16:05.499
and it turns out
we got picture-in-picture.

16:05.610 --> 16:07.449
You know, I appreciate it,
but I got to go.

16:07.761 --> 16:09.284
It's really hot in here.

16:12.113 --> 16:14.207
<i>Yep-- turns out Mike</i>
<i>wasn't as fine as he thought</i>

16:14.307 --> 16:15.650
<i>with Axl being gone.</i>

16:28.813 --> 16:32.102
- Still here, dad.
- Oh. Sorry.

16:34.447 --> 16:35.912
Hey, you want to
watch the game?

16:36.040 --> 16:37.270
No, I do not.

16:43.757 --> 16:45.639
Uh. Uh.

16:45.732 --> 16:47.621
Darrin! Darrin!
Wait up. Wait up.

16:47.757 --> 16:49.567
Sorry.
I take abnormally big steps.

16:49.762 --> 16:51.074
I'm hard to keep up with.

16:51.303 --> 16:52.533
Uh, listen.

16:53.441 --> 16:54.829
How do I say this?

16:55.589 --> 16:57.793
Okay, uh, ever since
Axl's been gone,

16:57.898 --> 17:00.622
I don't know if you've noticed,
but I have just sort of

17:00.719 --> 17:02.977
blossomed into
this whole new person,

17:03.131 --> 17:05.582
and I started thinking more
about what I want,

17:05.757 --> 17:08.017
and I just kind of
wondered if--

17:08.132 --> 17:09.163
Hey, dude.

17:09.267 --> 17:10.220
Oh, hi, Angel.

17:10.335 --> 17:11.366
Angel, this is Sue.

17:11.473 --> 17:12.772
Sue, this is Angel.

17:12.865 --> 17:15.844
Angel's in the cosmetology
program at Orson Beauty Academy.

17:15.970 --> 17:18.018
We share a parking lot
and a cafeteria with them.

17:18.133 --> 17:19.542
Cool!

17:19.695 --> 17:21.885
Ooh, I really like your nails.

17:22.003 --> 17:23.691
Thanks, yeah,
I posted them on Facebook,

17:23.786 --> 17:26.719
and so far
I've gotten 16 likes.

17:26.847 --> 17:29.266
Ah! Amazing!

17:29.352 --> 17:31.348
So, can we go somewhere
and talk?

17:31.481 --> 17:32.664
We were going to the movies.

17:32.759 --> 17:34.256
Oh. Okay. Yeah.

17:34.337 --> 17:37.355
I guess we can all do that,
and then we can talk after?

17:37.607 --> 17:39.149
No, I meant the two of us.

17:39.238 --> 17:40.368
Oh.

17:40.491 --> 17:43.247
Well, that's weird,
'cause what is Angel gonna do?

17:43.364 --> 17:44.543
She's right there.

17:44.645 --> 17:47.629
Sue, Angel and I go to
the movies every Sunday night.

17:47.724 --> 17:49.442
Well, that just
makes it worse, Darrin,

17:49.530 --> 17:51.054
